cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of deep learning models in various domains, including supervised learning datasets, reinforcement learning domains, and generative model training. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, given the focus on training large batches and the use of gradient noise scale as a predictor, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
